Apedunculata

is a valid genus, and a parasite of prochilodontid gills characterized by the following combination of characters: 
1
) vaginal opening sinistrolateral slightly sclerotized, opening interiorly at the level of the copulatory complex, 
2
) coiled male copulatory organ with counterclockwise rings, 
3
) accessory piece distal and not articulated, and 
4
) disk-shaped body without peduncle.
